#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-raw-vbi.rst:266
msgid ""
"A VBI device may support :ref:`read/write <rw>` and/or streaming (:ref:"
"`memory mapping <mmap>` or :ref:`user pointer <userp>`) I/O. The latter "
"bears the possibility of synchronizing video and VBI data by using buffer "
"timestamps."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-raw-vbi.rst:271
msgid ""
"Remember the :ref:`VIDIOC_STREAMON <VIDIOC_STREAMON>` ioctl and the first :c:"
"func:`read()`, :c:func:`write()` and :c:func:`select()` call can be resource "
"allocation points returning an ``EBUSY`` error code if the required hardware "
"resources are temporarily unavailable, for example the device is already in "
"use by another process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-raw-vbi.rst:279
msgid ""
"ASK: Amplitude-Shift Keying. A high signal level represents a '1' bit, a low "
"level a '0' bit."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../userspace-api/media/v4l/dev-raw-vbi.rst:283
msgid ""
"A few devices may be unable to sample VBI data at all but can extend the "
"video capture window to the VBI region."
